pyrex: pyrex (A compiler/language for writing Python extension modules)
pyrex:
pyrex: Pyrex is Python with C types.  It is specially designed to allow you
pyrex: to write extension modules for Python that have the speed of C and
pyrex: the simplicity and readability of Python.  You write your code in a
pyrex: Python-like language with C-typed variables, then use the pyrexc
pyrex: compiler to transform it into a C representation. This is useful
pyrex: for speeding up critical sections of your Python code or wrapping an
pyrex: external library.
pyrex: http://www.cosc.canterbury.ac.nz/~greg/python/Pyrex/
pyrex: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
